	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I remember we already discussed something like this... I can't find the topic now, but we did.
<br />
<br />It would be great if instead of complete mappers the emulators emulated components, and a cartridge description would indicate the parts that are used and how they are wired up. As long as the emulator knew the chips, it would be able to simulate any cartridge that used them.
<br />
<br />That would even allow homebrewers to create new boards without the pain that is getting an unused iNES number and having the scheme implemented in different emulators.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


