	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />How about just the simplest mappers being specified dynamically.
<br />
<br />Something that would handle the mappers that just do bankswitching and mirroring selection without modes.
<br />
<br />You just need to specify where the bytes you write to are, what address mask to use, how wide the banks are, and how the bits are shifted, AND'd and OR'd together to create the bank selection for PRG and CHR as well as mirroring.
<br />
<br />I could see these mappers being done this way:
<br />2, 3, 7, 11, 33, 34, 46, 57, 66, 70, 71, 75, 78, 79, 80, 89, 93, 94, 97, 107, 113, 140, 152, 164, 180, 184, 185, 193, 203, 207, 232, 240, 246
<br />Consider this the "List of simple mappers".

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


