<br />Well, "cheap" can have different meanings depending on the type of cart you're talking about. For a devcart, $200 is an acceptable price (not great, but being a one time deal most people would be able to make the sacrifice eventually), but production carts of the games made with that devcart must be way cheaper, because nobody will pay $200 for a single NES game.

		

